race.comment: SOUTH HOBA (9) is first-up today for the new stable having made the move from Victoria. Her recent trial was solid and the booking of Pike suggests she's ready to fire. Has shown good ability in her short career to date and she can kick off on a winning note. BOUSSAC (4)  stuck on well first-up over 1200m to be beaten 0.8L when the race favourite. This looks to shape similarly, but he should be better for the fresh run after only 1 trial coming into this campaign. Can improve sharply now and he looks the main danger. CRYPTIC JOY (5) ran over the top to score in a photo finish over 1200m here last start and was on the quick turnaround there. CJP remains in the saddle and he should be able to sit handy again from a good barrier. Can repeat the dose. ACROSS GENERATIONS (7) is better than he showed last start and can return to form as he drops in grade. OISIN (3) will be fitter for two trials coming in and can play a role on resumption.
